.\" parse-manager(1) - Lime parser plugin management tool
.\" Man page generated for the Lime Parser Generator project.
.TH PARSE-MANAGER 1 "2026-04-23" "Lime 0.1" "Lime Parser Tools"
.SH NAME
parse-manager \- manage Lime parser plugins at runtime
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B parse-manager
.RI [ options ]
.I command
.RI [ args... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B parse-manager
is a command-line tool for loading, inspecting, testing, and benchmarking
parser plugins built with the Lime parser generator. It uses the
.B ParserManager
library API to dynamically load parser plugins from shared libraries and
manage them at runtime.
.PP
Parser plugins implement the
.B LimeParserPlugin
interface and are typically built as shared libraries (.so files) that
export the
.B lime_plugin_entry
symbol.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-search\-path " " \fIdir\fR
Add a directory to the plugin search path. The manager will search
these directories when loading a plugin with a relative path.
May be specified multiple times.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-validate
Enable snapshot validation on load. When a plugin creates a snapshot,
the manager will call the plugin's
.B validate_snapshot
callback (if available) before making the snapshot active.
.TP
.BR \-j ", " \-\-jit
Enable automatic JIT compilation. When a plugin creates a snapshot and
advertises JIT capability, the manager will compile the action tables
to machine code for faster parsing.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress non-essential output.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage summary and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS list
.B parse-manager list
.PP
Show all currently loaded parser plugins in a table format. Displays
the plugin handle, name, version, active status, type (dynamic/static),
and capabilities.
.SS load
.B parse-manager load
.I path
.PP
Load a parser plugin from a shared library at
.IR path .
The library must export the
.B lime_plugin_entry
function. On success, prints the assigned handle and plugin name.
.SS unload
.B parse-manager unload
.I name
.PP
Unload the plugin with the given name. Calls the plugin's
.B destroy()
callback and removes it from the registry. If the plugin was the
active parser, it is deactivated first.
.SS info
.B parse-manager info
.I name
.PP
Show detailed information about the named plugin, including version,
type, active status, and a checklist of supported capabilities.
.SS activate
.B parse-manager activate
.I name
.RI [ grammar-file ]
.PP
Set the named plugin as the active parser. If
.I grammar-file
is provided, the plugin's
.B create_snapshot()
callback is called to produce a parser snapshot from the grammar.
.SS test
.B parse-manager test
.I name
.I input-file
.PP
Parse the given input file using the named parser plugin. Reports
success or failure and the time taken.
.SS compare
.B parse-manager compare
.I name1
.I name2
.I input-file
.PP
Parse the same input file with two different parser plugins and
compare the results. Reports whether both parsers agree and their
relative performance.
.SS benchmark
.B parse-manager benchmark
.I name
.I file
.RI [ file... ]
.PP
Run a performance benchmark of the named parser on one or more input
files. Automatically scales the number of iterations based on file
size. Reports per-file timing, overall throughput, and a summary.
.SS version
.B parse-manager version
.PP
Show version information for the tool, plugin ABI, parser library,
and JIT availability.
.SS help
.B parse-manager help
.RI [ command ]
.PP
Show help for a specific command, or list all available commands.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, plugin not found, parse failure, etc.).
.SH EXAMPLES
Load a plugin and list it:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ parse-manager load /usr/lib/lime/sql_parser.so
Loaded plugin 'sql_parser' (handle 1, version 1.0.0)

$ parse-manager list
ID    Name                  Version     Active    Type      Capabilities
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1     sql_parser            1.0.0         *       dynamic   snapshot, extensible
.fi
.RE
.PP
Test a parser on a SQL file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ parse-manager activate sql_parser grammar.y
Activated parser 'sql_parser' with grammar 'grammar.y'.

$ parse-manager test sql_parser query.sql
Parsing 'query.sql' with plugin 'sql_parser'...
OK: Parse succeeded
  Time: 0.342 ms
  Input: 1024 bytes from 'query.sql'
.fi
.RE
.PP
Compare two parser versions:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ parse-manager load parser_v1.so
$ parse-manager load parser_v2.so
$ parse-manager compare parser_v1 parser_v2 big_query.sql
Comparing parsers on 'big_query.sql' (65536 bytes):

  Parser                Result      Time (ms)
--------------------------------------------------
  parser_v1             OK          12.450
  parser_v2             OK          8.230

Both parsers succeeded.
'parser_v2' was 1.5x faster.
.fi
.RE
.PP
Benchmark a parser:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ parse-manager benchmark sql_parser tests/*.sql
Benchmarking parser 'sql_parser' on 5 file(s):

  File                                      Size (B)      Iters    Avg (ms)  Result
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  tests/simple.sql                              128       1000       0.012  OK
  tests/complex.sql                            8192         10       1.234  OK
  tests/huge.sql                              65536         10      12.345  OK

Summary:
  Files:    5 total, 5 succeeded, 0 failed
  Total:    73856 bytes
  Avg time: 4.530 ms per file
  Throughput: 16.3 MB/s (approximate)
.fi
.RE
